<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1581">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/64.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Hamm</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>State to General Carranza that at request of German Embassy, this
                                city, Department has instructed you to ask him to order release to
                                owner, of hardware store in San Pedro de Las Colonias, Coahuila, and
                                ranch twelve or fifteen miles east of city, both belonging to Mrs.
                                Helena Pfeiffer, a German subject, and seized by Constitutionalists,
                                including quantity of wheat and cotton on ranch. Store said to be in
                                charge of Colonel C. Benavides.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>